abstract: The event, hosted by Lulac, played out amid fights over adding a citizenship question to the census, the crisis at the border and planned raids on immigrant families.
snippet: The event, hosted by Lulac, played out amid fights over adding a citizenship question to the census, the crisis at the border and planned raids on immigrant families.
lead_paragraph: MILWAUKEE — Senator Elizabeth Warren accused President Trump of stirring “hate.” Julián Castro said the president had acted “like a dictator.” The Trump administration’s actions, warned Beto O’Rourke, threaten to “stain” the nation’s conscience.

abstract: Fourteen candidates are assured a place onstage. The rest are battling it out for six remaining slots. In September, things get tougher.
snippet: Fourteen candidates are assured a place onstage. The rest are battling it out for six remaining slots. In September, things get tougher.
lead_paragraph: With just four weeks to go until the second set of Democratic presidential primary debates, a handful of lower-tier candidates are in danger of missing them. A single percentage point of support in one poll could be the difference between getting invited to Detroit and being left off the debate stage.

abstract: An issue that united the party in 2018 has potential to fracture it in 2020.
snippet: An issue that united the party in 2018 has potential to fracture it in 2020.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It was a command as much as a question, intended to put an end to months of equivocating and obfuscating on the issue: Which of the Democratic presidential candidates on the debate stage supported abolishing private health insurance in favor of a single government-run plan? Show of hands, please.
